1. 

If you are have ISMEAR = 0 and want to know which SIGMA value is good. Please start from a reasonable value and do a test vasp run, 
for example SIGMA=0.1 and check the entropy per atom from OUTCAR with the bash command below

awk '/NIONS/ {n=$NF} /entropy T\*S/ {e=$NF} END {printf "%.4f meV/atom\n", e/n*1000}' OUTCAR

The value it returns has to be around or smaller than 1 meV per atom


2. 

If you have a metallic system, which means your system has bands smoothly crossing the fermi level, you can use ISMEAR=0 and ISMEAR=1. Usually we recommend ISMEAR=1 for metallic system
because usually it converges faster with the same K-resolution compared with ISMEAR=0. 

But you can still use ISMEAR=0 with a very small SIGMA(e.g., 0.02) for metallic system. This is a general choice but not optimal for metallic system.
